## Cloudflare Worker (the brain)

The Worker handles three responsibilities:

### 1. Domain routing
Every incoming request is matched to a tenant:
- Check the `Host` header against KV store (`domain -> tenant_id`)
- Load tenant config from D1 (API key, template, branding, active status)
- If no match, return a generic 404 page

### 2. BRP API proxy
The checkout SPA never talks to BRP directly. All BRP requests go through the Worker:
- `GET /api/locations` - fetch locations for this tenant's BRP account
- `GET /api/products?locationId=X` - fetch products at a location
- `POST /api/member/lookup` - check if email exists in BRP
- `POST /api/member/create` - create new member in BRP
- `POST /api/payment/create` - generate BRP payment link
- The Worker injects the tenant's BRP API credentials on every proxied request
- Cache product/location data in KV with 15-minute TTL (these rarely change)
- Never expose BRP API keys to the client

### 3. Admin API
Authenticated endpoints for the admin panel:
- `POST /admin/auth/login` - login, return JWT
- `GET /admin/tenant` - get tenant config
- `PUT /admin/tenant` - update branding, template selection
- `PUT /admin/tenant/brp` - update BRP API credentials (validate before saving)
- `POST /admin/tenant/domain` - add custom domain
- `GET /admin/preview` - return a preview URL with draft config

